The evidence with the title 'For most workers, real wages have barely budged for decades | pew ... ' says Oct 9, 2014  ... For most U.S. workers , inflation-adjusted wages have been flat or falling for decades , regardless of whether the economy has been adding or subtracting  ... When compared with the pre - Great Recession years of 2006 and 2007, when the average hourly wage often increased by around 4 % year-over-year. 
